[[File:Portrait of Revd. John Bulmer, Haverfordwest (4672795).jpg|thumb|Portrait of Revd. John Bulmer, Haverfordwest]]
'''John Bulmer''' (1784 - 1857) was an Independent minister. He was born and grew up in [[Yorkshire]], England, and was  educated for the Congregational Ministry at Rotherham (Masborough) Independent College.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hymnary.org/person/Bulmer_J1|title=John Bulmer - Hymnary.org|publisher=}}</ref> He moved to [[Wales]] as pastor of Albany Meeting House, [[Haverfordwest]] in 1813. Whilst there he worked on and published a number of volumes of verse, sermons, and other religious material.

In 1840 he left [[Haverfordwest]] for a position in [[Rugeley]]. He held further ministerial positions in [[Bristol]], [[Newbury, Berkshire|Newbury]], and (after an interval) at Langmore and [[Ruxton, Herefordshire|Ruxton]] near [[Ross-on-Wye|Ross]].

He died in 1857.
<ref>{{cite web|title=John Bulmer|url=http://wbo.llgc.org.uk/en/s-BULM-JOH-1784.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=23 August 2016}}</ref>

