{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}
'''Sayyed Ajami''' (سيد عجمي) was arrested in September 1998 in the United Kingdom, and accused of membership in [[Egyptian Islamic Jihad|al-Jihad]].<ref name="csisJaballah">[[Canadian Security Intelligence Service]], [http://cas-ncr-nter03.cas-satj.gc.ca/rss/Jaballah.pdf Summary of the Security Intelligence Report concerning Mahmoud Jaballah], 22 February 2008. Appendix A.</ref>

He was arrested as part of Operation Challenge, which arrested seven men living in Britain through use of the [[Prevention of Terrorism Act 1989]], accusing them of links to al-Jihad.<ref name="time">Hoge, Warren. [[New York Times]], "Britain arrests 7 suspected of links to Bin Laden", 24 September 1998</ref><ref>[[The Guardian]], [https://www.theguardian.com/uk/1999/mar/16/richardnortontaylor.ianblack Police hold Islam cleric 'in fishing expedition'], 16 March 1999</ref><ref>[[Associated Press]], "Police continue questioning of seven arrested in terrorism probe ", 24 September 1998</ref><ref>Al-Sharq al-Awsat, [http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&p_multi=BBAB&d_place=BBAB&p_theme=newslibrary2&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F99F792394C7970&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Position of Fundamentalists in Britain], 23 March 1999</ref><ref>[[UPI]], "Egypt Helps Britain Round Up Terrorists", 25 September 1998</ref> One of the men was charged with possession of a weapon.<ref>Al-Sharq al-Awsat, "British Muslims cited on arrest of fundamentalists", 29 September 1998</ref><ref>Al-Sharq al-Awsat, "Egyptian Information said to have helped in UK arrests", 28 September 1998</ref> Six months after the arrests, British Muslims staged a demonstration in front of [[10 Downing Street]] to protest the continued incarceration of the seven men.<ref>al-Sharq al-Awsat, "Islamic fundamentalist groups planning 12th March Downing St. Protest", 5 March 1999</ref>

He had previously been arrested multiple times throughout the 1980s.<ref>[[Jarret Brachman|Brachman, Jarret]]. "Global Jihadism", p. 165</ref>

